Using the equation in Step 10, the price of the put option is solved as follows: 

&nbsp;

$$\begin{aligned}
\textbf{P}&=\$60\times2.71828^{-(0.0270)(0.33)}+\$10.88-\$64\\[15pt]
&=\$60\times2.71828^{-0.00891}+\$10.88-\$64\\[15pt]
&=\$60\times0.9911+\$10.88-\$64\\[15pt]
&=\$59.47+\$10.88-\$64\\[15pt]
&=\boxed{\$6.35}
\end{aligned}$$

Hence, the value of call option is $6.35.
